The Office of National Drug Control Policy (ONDCP) hosted a policy briefing on the drug abuse epidemic in America, which was attended by First Lady Melania Trump. The ONDCP Director, Jim Carroll, expressed his appreciation for the Trump Administration's commitment to saving lives and highlighted the work being done by ONDCP and its partners across the nation. During the briefing, Mrs. Trump and Director Carroll discussed the challenges of the opioid crisis and the efforts being made to prevent drug abuse, provide treatment for addiction, and reduce the availability of illegal drugs in the United States.